A POLICEMAN has been injured after being stabbed in the leg while attending a disturbance in Glasgow.The officer was taken to hospital following the incident in Hutton Drive in Govan.A Police Scotland spokeswoman said his injuries were not life threatening.She said: &quot;Around 1.05pm, while attending an incident in the Govan area, a Police Scotland officer was injured.&quot;The officer has been taken to hospital for treatment and his injuries are not life threatening.&quot;Two men have been detained in connection with a disturbance in the area and inquiries are continuing to establish the exact circumstance.&quot;Police are carrying out inquires to establish the exact circumstances of the incident.Anyone with information is asked to contact Govan CID via the non-emergency number 101.